    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Metal and plastic identification tages, often worn in pairs, by military personnel around their necks, carrying such information as name, rank, serial number, religious affiliation, and blood type; so-called because they broadly resemble the common tags used for pets. Modern tags may include digital information.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000105490/Merriam-Webster Dictionary [online] (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079670/Whitaker, Unspeakable Love (2006)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chapas de identificación de metal llevadas en pares por personal militar alrededor del cuello, conteniendo información tal como el nombre, el grado, el número de serie, la afiliación religiosa y el tipo de sangre.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
